  "created": "2025-10-15",
  "description": "E. coli heat shock response is mediated by alternative sigma factor \u03c332 (RpoH) which directs RNA polymerase to heat shock gene promoters. Under normal conditions, \u03c332 is unstable (t1/2 ~1 min) due to DnaK/DnaJ/GrpE chaperones targeting it for FtsH protease degradation. Heat stress causes protein misfolding, titrating away chaperones. Free \u03c332 accumulates, transcribes ~30 heat shock genes including DnaK/J, GroEL/ES, ClpB, Lon, FtsH. This creates negative feedback as newly synthesized chaperones re-sequester \u03c332.",
  "id": "ecoli_e._coli_heat_shock_response",
  "keywords": [
    "heat shock",
    "\u03c332",
    "RpoH",
    "DnaK",
    "GroEL",
    "chaperones",
    "protein folding"
  ],
  "lastUpdated": "2025-10-15",
